The Global Citizen Festival started in 2012 and is an expansion of the Global Poverty Project, an international interest organization that struggles to end poverty by increasing the number of active opponents.
To receive a free ticket to the event (if you do not want to pay for a VIP ticket), concert walkers must perform a number of tasks or "actions". e.g. do volunteer work, write to a world leader, make a phone call or some other meaningful action that can raise awareness about the goal of ending poverty.
